
class property vs instance property
use static keyword to define class level property.
This is usually used to define routes for screen

With React Navigation 5.x, we need to pass the configuration when defining the screen:
<Stack.Screen
  name="Profile"
  component={ProfileScreen}
  options={{ headerShown: false }}
/>

we can't use 
static navigationOptions = {
    headerShown: false,
  };
https://reactnavigation.org/docs/upgrading-from-4.x/

onslide pagingEnabled:
When true, the scroll view stops on multiples of the scroll view's size when scrolling. This can be used for horizontal pagination.

npm qs to parse object to query string
latlng-to-zip to convert latitude-longitude combination to zipcode

I am using github jobs as no API key is required


You must use an API key to authenticate each request to Google Maps Platform APIs
For calling google maps location data, we need API key. It can be generated from 
https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/geocoding/get-api-key
I have set restriction for the key to be used only through my expo ip 192.168.43.125
Save the key in the app.json file.
{
  "expo": {
    "ios": {
      "config": {
        "googleMapsApiKey": "YOUR_GOOGLE_MAP_API_KEY_HERE"
      }
    },
    "android": {
      "config": {
        "googleMaps": {
          "apiKey": "YOUR_GOOGLE_MAP_API_KEY_HERE"
        }
      }
    },
  }
}

